WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:12.913 --> 00:00:14.847
More.

3
00:00:22.973 --> 00:00:24.640
Another.

4
00:00:26.477 --> 00:00:28.321
Careful. señor.

5
00:00:28.345 --> 00:00:30.657
Hot day like today.

6
00:00:30.681 --> 00:00:33.593
too much oil in the machine

7
00:00:33.617 --> 00:00:36.779
can cause it to blow a gasket.

8
00:00:36.803 --> 00:00:41.301
There are two kinds
of men in this world.

9
00:00:41.325 --> 00:00:42.469
Those who drink

10
00:00:42.493 --> 00:00:44.788
and those who pour.

11
00:00:44.812 --> 00:00:47.696
Shut up and fill my glass.

12
00:00:57.307 --> 00:01:00.687
Hey. you two.

13
00:01:00.711 --> 00:01:01.805
Yes. you.

14
00:01:01.829 --> 00:01:04.825
I used to be just like you.

15
00:01:04.849 --> 00:01:08.711
Worked dirt for the
man till my hands bled.

16
00:01:08.735 --> 00:01:10.013
But no more.

17
00:01:10.037 --> 00:01:14.651
Because I learned that a
man can never drink his fill

18
00:01:14.675 --> 00:01:17.354
by waiting in line for the tap.

19
00:01:17.378 --> 00:01:19.222
Listen to him.

20
00:01:19.246 --> 00:01:21.413
He can teach you something.

21
00:01:24.050 --> 00:01:26.851
Hey. how you doing. boss?

22
00:01:29.573 --> 00:01:33.452
Good to see you. my friend.

23
00:01:33.476 --> 00:01:37.807
You know. I never pegged
you for such a deep thinker.

24
00:01:37.831 --> 00:01:40.126
I keep thinking I
should write a book.

25
00:01:40.150 --> 00:01:42.183
Maybe. maybe...

26
00:01:45.121 --> 00:01:49.736
So. what brings you to this
burro's asshole of a town?

27
00:01:49.760 --> 00:01:51.960
I knew I would find you here.

28
00:01:53.881 --> 00:01:57.344
Don't you have
something to deliver?

29
00:01:57.368 --> 00:01:59.168
Cutting it close. aren't you?

30
00:02:00.570 --> 00:02:03.482
Ah. lots of time.

31
00:02:03.506 --> 00:02:08.438
Tortuga may be slow out
of the gate. but he always...

32
00:02:08.462 --> 00:02:10.139
Finishes first.

33
00:02:10.163 --> 00:02:12.676
Yes. I know. Just
like your namesake.

34
00:02:12.700 --> 00:02:15.946
I like the way
you talk. Tortuga.

35
00:02:15.970 --> 00:02:17.848
Yeah?

36
00:02:17.872 --> 00:02:20.450
You've got such
a way with words.

37
00:02:20.474 --> 00:02:25.188
They flow like a waterfall.

38
00:02:25.212 --> 00:02:27.173
I like that about you.

39
00:02:27.197 --> 00:02:28.896
<i>Salud. Salud.</i>

40
00:02:32.068 --> 00:02:37.383
I'm so stupid. I
missed your birthday.

41
00:02:37.407 --> 00:02:39.018
No. I feel terrible.

42
00:02:39.042 --> 00:02:42.755
So bad I came all the way
here to this burro's asshole

43
00:02:42.779 --> 00:02:44.557
to give you your present.

44
00:02:44.581 --> 00:02:46.292
Present?

45
00:02:46.316 --> 00:02:48.911
Come on. no need to
go through the trouble.

46
00:02:48.935 --> 00:02:51.053
Forget it. I wanted to.

47
00:02:52.656 --> 00:02:54.323
I have it for you in the back.

48
00:02:56.560 --> 00:02:59.294
Back there? Yes.
Come. Follow me.

49
00:03:13.193 --> 00:03:15.771
It's perfect!

50
00:03:15.795 --> 00:03:17.957
Do you really like it?

51
00:03:17.981 --> 00:03:19.242
Oh.

52
00:03:19.266 --> 00:03:21.277
I love it!

53
00:03:21.301 --> 00:03:23.679
What a great pet it will make.

54
00:03:23.703 --> 00:03:25.231
Thank you. boss!

55
00:03:25.255 --> 00:03:27.100
Excellent.

56
00:03:27.124 --> 00:03:29.803
Let me sign it for you.

57
00:03:29.827 --> 00:03:31.242
Let me sign it...

58
00:03:33.046 --> 00:03:38.116
"For the big talker."

59
00:04:38.112 --> 00:04:40.790
He's still breathing.

60
00:04:40.814 --> 00:04:45.428
Well. by the looks of him. he
has no idea how close he came.

61
00:04:45.452 --> 00:04:49.966
I'm assuming Saul Goodman
doesn't need to know.

62
00:04:49.990 --> 00:04:52.190
Mum's the word.

63
00:05:10.644 --> 00:05:13.011
<i>♪ Old MacDonald
had a farm E-I-E-I-O ♪</i>

64
00:05:14.281 --> 00:05:16.676
<i>♪ And on this farm
He had a duck ♪</i>

65
00:05:16.700 --> 00:05:18.277
♪ E-I-E-I-O ♪

66
00:05:18.301 --> 00:05:21.147
<i>♪ With a quack. quack here
And a quack. quack there ♪</i>

67
00:05:23.140 --> 00:05:26.820
♪ Old MacDonald
had a farm E-I-E-I-O ♪

68
00:05:28.846 --> 00:05:30.957
<i>♪ Old MacDonald
had a farm E-I-E-I-O ♪</i>

69
00:05:30.981 --> 00:05:34.449
Oh. son of a bitch.

70
00:05:48.615 --> 00:05:49.826
Hang on. baby.

71
00:06:02.195 --> 00:06:04.040
<i>Hello.</i>

72
00:06:04.064 --> 00:06:05.980
Walt? Are you in the house?

73
00:06:08.085 --> 00:06:11.536
<i>Oh. hey. Skyler. Yeah. it's me.</i>

74
00:06:13.190 --> 00:06:15.969
What? What the hell
are you doing in there?

75
00:06:15.993 --> 00:06:17.653
<i>I'm back.</i>

76
00:06:17.677 --> 00:06:20.439
No. no. you're not back. Walt.

77
00:06:20.463 --> 00:06:23.343
You're not back.
Get... Get out of there.

78
00:06:23.367 --> 00:06:25.862
<i>Well. it's... It's my
house too. Skyler.</i>

79
00:06:25.886 --> 00:06:29.115
I'm staying. End of story.

80
00:06:29.139 --> 00:06:32.452
We had an agreement. <i>I
didn't agree to anything.</i>

81
00:06:32.476 --> 00:06:34.370
<i>Now. look. just come on inside</i>

82
00:06:34.394 --> 00:06:37.023
<i>and we'll talk this
through. okay?</i>

83
00:06:37.047 --> 00:06:39.275
No. No. There's
nothing to talk about.

84
00:06:39.299 --> 00:06:43.546
I am not coming in
there until you get out.

85
00:06:43.570 --> 00:06:48.350
<i>Well. suit yourself.</i>

86
00:06:48.374 --> 00:06:50.019
Walt.

87
00:06:50.043 --> 00:06:51.643
Walt?

88
00:07:16.119 --> 00:07:18.881
What is wrong with you?

89
00:07:18.905 --> 00:07:21.317
Skyler. I have every
right to be here.

90
00:07:21.341 --> 00:07:23.369
No. you don't.

91
00:07:23.393 --> 00:07:26.906
You don't live here anymore.
We're getting a divorce.

92
00:07:26.930 --> 00:07:28.557
I don't agree to a divorce.

93
00:07:28.581 --> 00:07:30.531
Well. it's not up to you.

94
00:07:32.035 --> 00:07:34.764
If you don't get out
of here right now.

95
00:07:34.788 --> 00:07:36.199
I'm gonna call the police

96
00:07:36.223 --> 00:07:40.003
and I'm going to
tell them everything.

97
00:07:40.027 --> 00:07:42.777
I mean it. Walt.

98
00:07:45.782 --> 00:07:48.349
There's the phone.

99
00:08:06.119 --> 00:08:07.919
It's ringing.

100
00:08:11.541 --> 00:08:14.654
<i>Albuquerque Police Department.</i>

101
00:08:14.678 --> 00:08:17.545
<i>Operator number 314.
How may I help you?</i>

102
00:08:19.132 --> 00:08:23.078
<i>Albuquerque Police
Department. How may I help you?</i>

103
00:08:23.102 --> 00:08:28.518
Yes. I. uh... I want to
report a disturbance. please.

104
00:08:28.542 --> 00:08:32.577
No. no. it's not... It's
not exactly. it's. um...

105
00:08:33.747 --> 00:08:37.126
It's a domestic issue.

106
00:08:37.150 --> 00:08:38.649
Okay.

107
00:08:42.205 --> 00:08:43.971
They're connecting me.

108
00:08:45.742 --> 00:08:48.554
Right hand to
God. I will tell them.

109
00:08:48.578 --> 00:08:51.290
Do what you have to do. Skyler.

110
00:08:51.314 --> 00:08:55.828
This family is everything to me.

111
00:08:55.852 --> 00:08:59.665
Without it. I have
nothing to lose.

112
00:08:59.689 --> 00:09:00.689
Fine.

113
00:09:03.459 --> 00:09:05.905
Yes. My name is Skyler White.

114
00:09:05.929 --> 00:09:09.142
I need police assistance
at my home right away.

115
00:09:09.166 --> 00:09:14.947
My soon-to-be-ex-husband
broke into my house.

116
00:09:14.971 --> 00:09:18.740
and I need an officer to
come and remove him.

117
00:09:20.293 --> 00:09:23.761
It's 308 Negra Arroyo Lane.

118
00:09:25.198 --> 00:09:28.767
Okay. Okay.

119
00:09:30.937 --> 00:09:32.637
Thank you.

120
00:09:38.261 --> 00:09:40.061
They're coming.

121
00:10:29.645 --> 00:10:32.207
Dad's here? WALT:
Great. he's home.

122
00:10:32.231 --> 00:10:33.926
Dad. Hey. son.

123
00:10:33.950 --> 00:10:36.028
How are you? Oh!

124
00:10:36.052 --> 00:10:38.864
Are... Are you back for good?

125
00:10:38.888 --> 00:10:41.100
Why are you home so soon?

126
00:10:41.124 --> 00:10:43.569
I... I'm not.

127
00:10:43.593 --> 00:10:44.870
Ah.

128
00:10:44.894 --> 00:10:47.540
Hey. I am starving. How
about a grilled cheese?

129
00:10:47.564 --> 00:10:49.275
Yeah. sure. You want one too?

130
00:10:49.299 --> 00:10:50.626
Walter. your dad and I

131
00:10:50.650 --> 00:10:52.728
have something
we need to discuss.

132
00:10:52.752 --> 00:10:56.348
When your sandwich is
ready. I'll bring it to your room.

133
00:10:56.372 --> 00:10:58.550
Mom. ca-can't it wait?

134
00:10:58.574 --> 00:11:00.920
I haven't seen
Dad in. like. forever.

135
00:11:00.944 --> 00:11:02.738
Walter? WALT: How was school?

136
00:11:02.762 --> 00:11:05.324
- It was good.
- Yeah? Homework?

137
00:11:05.348 --> 00:11:06.825
No. not really.

138
00:11:06.849 --> 00:11:09.130
What does that mean?

139
00:11:15.675 --> 00:11:17.174
Mmm.

140
00:11:18.345 --> 00:11:20.906
So are you gonna
be at work tomorrow?

141
00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:23.375
Yeah. that's the plan.

142
00:11:37.080 --> 00:11:39.925
Hello. ma'am. We were
called about a disturbance?

143
00:11:39.949 --> 00:11:44.085
It's more of a trespassing
situation. really. but...

144
00:11:45.305 --> 00:11:46.965
Yeah. that was me.

145
00:11:46.989 --> 00:11:51.526
You called the cops on Dad?

146
00:11:56.049 --> 00:11:58.794
I came home from
work. and he was back.

147
00:11:58.818 --> 00:12:01.147
He had just moved
back into the house.

148
00:12:01.171 --> 00:12:07.586
And I asked him to leave.
but he won't listen. I just...

149
00:12:07.610 --> 00:12:11.457
I want him out. I want
him out of the house.

150
00:12:11.481 --> 00:12:12.591
Okay. Mrs. White.

151
00:12:12.615 --> 00:12:15.127
there's a couple
questions I need to ask you.

152
00:12:15.151 --> 00:12:17.279
It's important you
answer honestly.

153
00:12:17.303 --> 00:12:19.181
Did he strike you?

154
00:12:19.205 --> 00:12:20.416
No.

155
00:12:20.440 --> 00:12:21.884
Has he ever hit you?

156
00:12:21.908 --> 00:12:24.687
No. This is not about violence.

157
00:12:24.711 --> 00:12:27.006
This is about trespassing.

158
00:12:27.030 --> 00:12:30.743
About him being
here against my will.

159
00:12:30.767 --> 00:12:31.977
Okay. Trespassing.

160
00:12:32.001 --> 00:12:35.464
You're divorced. then?
No. working on it. Um...

161
00:12:35.488 --> 00:12:37.633
Right now. were separated.

162
00:12:37.657 --> 00:12:39.035
Legally separated?

163
00:12:39.059 --> 00:12:42.238
Well. there's not a court
order. if that's what you mean.

164
00:12:42.262 --> 00:12:45.274
But we've been living
apart for almost two weeks.

165
00:12:45.298 --> 00:12:46.291
give or take.

166
00:12:46.315 --> 00:12:47.827
I-I changed the locks.

167
00:12:47.851 --> 00:12:50.729
Isn't that breaking
and entering?

168
00:12:50.753 --> 00:12:52.848
Whose name is on the title?

169
00:12:52.872 --> 00:12:55.133
Both of us. It's...
It's jointly owned.

170
00:12:55.157 --> 00:12:58.137
We can't arrest a man for
breaking into his own house.

171
00:12:58.161 --> 00:13:01.023
Not without a court order
requiring he stays away.

172
00:13:01.047 --> 00:13:03.275
Unless he's threatened
you or the kids.

173
00:13:03.299 --> 00:13:04.410
No. Not...

174
00:13:04.434 --> 00:13:06.378
Not physically.

175
00:13:06.402 --> 00:13:09.682
But having him in
the house is just...

176
00:13:09.706 --> 00:13:14.108
It's... It's not a good
thing. Excuse me.

177
00:13:15.761 --> 00:13:18.991
I got her. honey. Come here.

178
00:13:19.015 --> 00:13:20.959
Here we go.

179
00:13:20.983 --> 00:13:25.765
You hungry? You
hungry? Here we go.

180
00:13:25.789 --> 00:13:28.383
Oh. That was it.

181
00:13:28.407 --> 00:13:31.370
I'm sorry. officer.
Where were we?

182
00:13:31.394 --> 00:13:33.038
Disagreements.

183
00:13:33.062 --> 00:13:37.677
Yes. well. we've
had our share of that.

184
00:13:37.701 --> 00:13:39.511
I haven't...

185
00:13:39.535 --> 00:13:42.370
I haven't been the most
attentive husband lately.

186
00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:47.003
Mrs. White. would this be easier

187
00:13:47.027 --> 00:13:49.194
if we stepped
outside for a minute?

188
00:13:51.998 --> 00:13:54.510
No.

189
00:13:54.534 --> 00:13:56.645
Nope.

190
00:13:56.669 --> 00:13:59.081
I'm fine right here.

191
00:13:59.105 --> 00:14:00.933
I'm gonna level with you. ma'am.

192
00:14:00.957 --> 00:14:02.735
If you want him
out of the house.

193
00:14:02.759 --> 00:14:04.119
you'll have to help me.

194
00:14:04.143 --> 00:14:07.390
Is it possible maybe he's
broken any laws that you know of?

195
00:14:07.414 --> 00:14:09.024
Anything at all.

196
00:14:09.048 --> 00:14:11.827
Anything that we can
work with here. just tell me.

197
00:14:11.851 --> 00:14:14.696
Even if it's just a suspicion.
I can work with that.

198
00:14:14.720 --> 00:14:17.132
I'll get him out of
the house for you.

199
00:14:17.156 --> 00:14:19.134
What's your take on all this?

200
00:14:19.158 --> 00:14:20.998
It's my mom's fault.

201
00:14:23.696 --> 00:14:26.325
She won't even
say what my dad did

202
00:14:26.349 --> 00:14:29.979
and it's because he
didn't do anything.

203
00:14:30.003 --> 00:14:32.648
I don't know why
she's being this way.

204
00:14:32.672 --> 00:14:38.087
My dad. he is a great guy.

205
00:14:38.111 --> 00:14:42.191
Son. it's not your mom's fault.

206
00:14:42.215 --> 00:14:44.081
Mrs. White.

207
00:14:47.637 --> 00:14:50.032
I'm sorry. ma'am.
There's no legal basis

208
00:14:50.056 --> 00:14:52.539
for us to remove your
husband from the house.

209
00:14:54.109 --> 00:14:57.122
Next time you feel things
are getting out of control.

210
00:14:57.146 --> 00:15:00.592
you should call this
number. It's the family hotline.

211
00:15:00.616 --> 00:15:02.816
I'd really look into
some counseling.

212
00:15:04.654 --> 00:15:06.265
Best of luck to you folks.

213
00:15:06.289 --> 00:15:09.073
Listen. thank you.
officers. We're sorry.

214
00:15:16.750 --> 00:15:19.762
Why you gotta...? Why
you gotta do this to Dad?

215
00:15:19.786 --> 00:15:21.330
Junior. wait. come on.

216
00:15:21.354 --> 00:15:23.755
Don't blame your
mother for this.

217
00:15:28.328 --> 00:15:29.794
Sorry.

218
00:15:47.063 --> 00:15:48.963
Welcome home.

219
00:16:32.274 --> 00:16:36.254
He lives. Happy
housewarming. kid.

220
00:16:36.278 --> 00:16:38.907
Don't look so glad
to see me. Thanks.

221
00:16:38.931 --> 00:16:42.628
Oh. interesting
decor. It's. uh. subtle.

222
00:16:42.652 --> 00:16:44.162
The whole minimalist thing

223
00:16:44.186 --> 00:16:46.432
never really blew
my hair back. but hey.

224
00:16:46.456 --> 00:16:49.885
So how are you doing?

225
00:16:49.909 --> 00:16:51.876
Staying clean?

226
00:16:53.446 --> 00:16:56.975
Good. I was kind of worried
that you were back to old habits

227
00:16:56.999 --> 00:16:59.694
since I didn't hear
from you. you know.

228
00:16:59.718 --> 00:17:01.463
You realize how stupid it is

229
00:17:01.487 --> 00:17:03.665
to ignore your
counsel's phone calls?

230
00:17:03.689 --> 00:17:05.434
What if I was trying to warn you

231
00:17:05.458 --> 00:17:08.170
the DEA was gonna kick
down your door? What then?

232
00:17:08.194 --> 00:17:10.039
Why don't you
spare me the sermon

233
00:17:10.063 --> 00:17:11.740
and get to why you're here?

234
00:17:11.764 --> 00:17:13.876
Fair enough.
Remember the other day

235
00:17:13.900 --> 00:17:15.277
when I brought up the idea

236
00:17:15.301 --> 00:17:18.213
of you getting back in
touch with your. uh. partner?

237
00:17:18.237 --> 00:17:20.816
Well. I kind of wanted
to re-float that boat.

238
00:17:20.840 --> 00:17:23.819
I'm not suggesting you
yourself get back to cooking.

239
00:17:23.843 --> 00:17:25.754
I mean. you being
in rehab and all.

240
00:17:25.778 --> 00:17:29.375
I only want you to convince
the master chef to do his thing.

241
00:17:29.399 --> 00:17:32.678
So. what do you say?

242
00:17:32.702 --> 00:17:34.230
Sure. man. Whatever.

243
00:17:34.254 --> 00:17:36.131
Okay. Whatever what?

244
00:17:36.155 --> 00:17:38.751
I mean. you gonna call him?

245
00:17:38.775 --> 00:17:40.352
I said I'll handle it.

246
00:17:40.376 --> 00:17:43.105
Now. bounce. will you? Please?

247
00:17:43.129 --> 00:17:44.911
Final thought.

248
00:17:46.081 --> 00:17:47.192
Look at this place.

249
00:17:47.216 --> 00:17:50.095
You're house-poor.
you got no bankroll.

250
00:17:50.119 --> 00:17:52.231
If you get the
maestro cooking again.

251
00:17:52.255 --> 00:17:54.349
I'll make it worth your while.

252
00:17:55.908 --> 00:17:57.058
Call him.

253
00:18:43.055 --> 00:18:47.169
<i>If you're trying to sell
me something. four words:</i>

254
00:18:47.193 --> 00:18:48.604
<i>"Do Not Call list."</i>

255
00:18:48.628 --> 00:18:51.161
<i>However. if you're
cool. leave it at the beep.</i>

256
00:19:13.536 --> 00:19:15.347
Schrader.

257
00:19:15.371 --> 00:19:17.772
